sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    box "Hardware Domain" #f9f9f9
        participant Code as Executing Instruction
        participant CPU as ARM Core (Hardware)
    end

    box "Software Domain" #e1f5fe
        participant Vector as Vector Table
        participant Entry as ASM Entry
        participant Handler as C Handler
    end
    
    Note over Code,Handler: SYNCHRONOUS EXCEPTION FLOW (Steady Phase)
    
    Code->>CPU: Trigger Exception<br/>(Undef / SVC / Abort)
    
    activate CPU
    Note right of CPU: **HARDWARE ACTIONS:**<br/>1. Mode Switch (SVC -> UND/ABT)<br/>2. Save PC -> LR_mode<br/>3. Save CPSR -> SPSR_mode<br/>4. Mask IRQ (I=1)
    
    Note right of CPU: **VECTOR CALCULATION:**<br/>Base = Read CP15 VBAR<br/>Offset = +0x04(Undef), +0x08(SVC)...<br/>Target = VBAR + Offset
    
    CPU->>Vector: Jump to Target Address
    deactivate CPU
    
    Note right of Vector: ldr pc, =exception_entry_xxx
    
    Vector->>Entry: Branch to Entry Stub
    activate Entry
    
    Note right of Entry: **CONTEXT SAVE:**<br/>1. push {r0-r12}<br/>2. push {lr, spsr}<br/>3. Align Stack (8-byte)
    
    Entry->>Handler: Call C Handler
    activate Handler
    
    Note right of Handler: **KERNEL LOGIC:**<br/>1. Read Fault Status (DFSR/IFSR)<br/>2. Diagnose Cause<br/>3. Decide: Halt or Recover
    
    alt Fatal Error (Current Phase)
        Handler->>Handler: System Halt (while 1)
        Note right of Handler: Kernel Panic
    else Recoverable (Future)
        Handler-->>Entry: Return Result
        deactivate Handler
        
        Note right of Entry: **CONTEXT RESTORE:**<br/>1. pop {spsr} -> msr spsr<br/>2. pop {lr, r0-r12}
        
        Entry->>CPU: Exception Return<br/>(movs pc, lr OR subs pc, lr, #N)
        deactivate Entry
        
        activate CPU
        Note right of CPU: **HARDWARE RETURN:**<br/>1. Restore CPSR from SPSR<br/>2. PC = LR (modified)<br/>3. Resume Execution
        CPU-->>Code: Continue
        deactivate CPU
    end